    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-04T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-04T01:00:00-05:00" n="1052"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1052">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/4061: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sparks</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-04T01:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 4, 1940—1 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>167. With reference to my despatch No. 1029, September 28.<note n="39"
                        xml:id="d1052fn1">Not printed.</note> The Fiscal Representative informed the
                    Minister of Finance that 200,000 gourdes could be added to the estimate of
                    revenues if the French commercial treaty<note n="40" xml:id="d1052fn2"
                        >Commercial Convention, with Protocol, between France and Haiti, signed at
                        Paris, June 24, 1938. For text, see <hi rend="italic">Le Moniteur</hi>, July
                        11, 1938, p. 451, and August 8, 1938, p. 515.</note> were cancelled. The
                    budget as finally drafted <pb facs="0921" n="909" xml:id="pg_909"/> does not
                    include this additional revenue. The Finance Minister declared to the Fiscal
                    Representative that the Minister of Foreign Affairs tenaciously opposed, pending
                    the outcome of his negotiations with the French Government which apparently are
                    only for the purpose of suspending the treaty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sparks</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
